cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.NI 

This paper deals with the dynamics of contagious spreading processes in complex contact networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since the paper specifically studies the spreading of epidemics in networks. The second likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) since the paper deals with designing efficient strategies to contain epidemic outbreaks. The third likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) since the paper deals with the dynamics of stochastic processes. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper presents a lower-bound on the decay rate of the number of nodes infected by a spreading process. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) since the paper deals with the spreading of epidemics in contact networks.
